= Camarilla Joins the Conspiracy

In Berlin, another meeting is scheduled between [+ nsdap_leader +] and Papen in Ribbentrop's villa in the evening, this time also joined by Hindenburg's son Oskar, and his chief of staff Otto Meissner. Goring and two other important <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span> are also in attendance. This meeting has been organized by Papen himself, and reached the most momentous decision of his life: his most promising way to return to power and get revenge against Schleicher was to concede the chancellorship to [+ nsdap_chancellor +].

Despite his eagerness to depose Schleicher, Oskar is no <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazi</span>, and even warns his father of the dangers of appointing [+ nsdap_chancellor +], pointing out that he rarely keeps his promises and his appointment would inevitably lead to a one-party dictatorship. 

Meissner, recognizing that the chancellor's hold on power was slipping decided that it was time to ingratiate himself with Schleicher's most likely successor, whether it be Papen or [+ nsdap_chancellor +].

